Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

Casting call - Stray Dog
Currently casting all roles for 10 minute graduate film based in Bristol and surrounding areas. 

Set in the 1930‚Äôs, Stray Dog follows two silent cinema owning brothers during the rise of the ‚ÄúTalkies‚Äù. Oz leaves his brother and sets up his travelling cinema with lover Nancy. They party and discover how it feels to be free, but grow apart when Oz can‚Äôt learn to be serious. Eventually, a car crash allows Oz to come to terms with who he‚Äôs become and reflect on the important things in life. 

As it‚Äôs a student film, we are seeking contributors on a voluntary basis, but food and travel expenses will be covered. 

Shoot length is a maximum of 5 days, and will take place between end of February and start of March (dates TBC). 

We would love to hear from you! Please email: ttpsfilm@yahoo.com

items.text:
CASTING CALL ‚Äì LIVERPOOL ACTORS WANTED 

We're casting for "They Were All Some Mothers' Sons" ‚Äì a powerful true story returning to the stage at Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot in May 2026.

This sell-out production tells the remarkable true story of German POWs detained in Huyton during WWII who fell in love with local women and chose to stay, becoming part of our community. 

Previously performed to packed houses in Liverpool and Germany.

Roles available:

 Jean ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Eleanor ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Marjorie ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Joey ‚Äì Young British RAF pilot, male, playing age 18-24

 Mother ‚Äì female, playing age 40+

 Father ‚Äì male, playing age 40+

Key dates:

 Auditions: First week of February

 Rehearsals: Mid-March to show

 Performances: 1st, 2nd May 2026 (possible 3rd date)

 Venue: Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot

This is a paid role (profit share)

This is Prescot's own heritage story‚Äîtold in the heart of Knowsley, where it all happened over 80 years ago. We're looking for passionate local talent to bring this living history to life.

To apply: Send your CV and headshot to howl.michael1963@yahoo.co.uk specifying which role and which production you want to audition for.

Please prepare a 2-minute monologue of your choice for audition.

The American Film Association Summit in Atlanta with **distributors, financiers, studio executives, theater owners, and filmmakers** all in the same room.

The goal isn‚Äôt gatekeeping or motivation. It‚Äôs practical, tactical conversations about how films actually get financed, distributed, and sustained in today‚Äôs market.

If you‚Äôre building projects and want real dialogue with people across the ecosystem, not panels or sales pitches, this will be worth your time I promise.

items.text:
ACTING IN LONG-FORM IMPROV
3-Hour Intensive with Arek Ziƒôtek
Go deeper into story, character, and relationships.
For improvisers with basic experience and curious newcomers ready to play.
This is a focused intensive (not a jam).
We move from core principles to advanced long-form tools, blending acting craft with improvisation to create grounded, honest scenes.
You‚Äôll work on:
‚Ä¢ Building believable characters in the moment
‚Ä¢ Emotional truth & listening
‚Ä¢ Relationships that drive long-form stories
‚Ä¢ Presence, commitment & clarity on stage
‚Ä¢ Sustaining scenes beyond jokes
Acting first. Comedy second. Real, playful, alive.
With Arek Ziƒôtek
Warsaw-based theatre teacher, trained in the Keith Johnstone tradition (Theatresports)
üìÜ Sunday ¬∑ Jan 25
‚è∞ 2:00‚Äì5:00 PM
üìç Po≈Çudnik 2.0 ¬∑ Wilcza 25, Warsaw
üé≠ Limited spots
Strengthen your craft. Deepen your scenes.
Leave with tools you can actually use on stage.

Get in soon:

https://fienta.com/pl/acting-storytelling-improv-workshop-with-arek-zietek-165241

items.text:
Casting Call for student filmüé≠üé¨
Comedy short film - 10 minutes 

A struggling theater show is made worse by a new member of the crew who‚Äôs inexperience makes it a night to remember.

Lee (male 20-30)

An ambitious theatre worker who is always wanting more out of life. Can be naive to the ways of the world but has blind optimism that gets him

through stressful times.

George (male 20-30)

A sarcastic, hardworking tech worker who struggles to find joy from his work. Wants to use his talents elsewhere but has no motivation to do so.

Jamie (female 25-35)

The theatre plays stressed out director who struggles with the demand of the actors and lack of backstage crew.

Expenses paid only

Shoot date: 12th-17th March 2026

Location: Aylesbury 

If interested contact: ruth.merry@outlook.com

üé≠ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì A PLACE NOT MINE** üé≠

We are casting for **A Place Not Mine**, a new original musical (cabaret style) exploring **belonging, identity, and chosen family**, set in a magical university world.

‚ú® **FINAL ROLE AVAILABLE** ‚ú®

‚ú® **ORIS** (Male, playing age 20‚Äì24)

üìç **Performance Dates:**
**5th & 6th July**
üìç **Drayton Arms Theatre**, London

üìç **Rehearsals:**
Late February / Early March
Approximately **one rehearsal per week**, scheduled around cast availability

üé≠ **Project Type:** Showcase production
This version of the project is **unpaid**, with the aim of documenting the work and sharing it with theatre makers and creatives. All performers will receive a **professional video recording of their performance** for personal use and showreels.

üì© **To apply:**
Please send your **CV / headshot** and a short introduction to:
üìß **emilvasilev296@gmail.com**

Feel free to share or tag anyone who might be interested!

üé∏ Durch eine Einladung in Instagram, durch den Musiker und Schauspieler Florian Thunemann, bin ich gestern auf dieses kleine Kultur-Universum gesto√üen: 

üïäÔ∏è ‚ÄûLong Erich & Friends‚Äú trifft ‚ÄûLohse Saiten‚Äú, von Blues, Rock und Folk bis Gypsy Swing. 

ü§ç Ich habe Florian zwei Fotos gemacht und heute am PC daraus ein kleines Video geformt, Gitarrenmusik darunter, Herz dar√ºber. 

üé∏ Dabei ist mir dieser Vers in den Kopf gekommen und ich lasse ihn genau so stehen: 

üïäÔ∏è "So wie Du Bilder 
zu Geschichten formst, 
formt der Groove Dich 
zu einem Menschen, 
der wieder im Takt atmet." 

ü§ç Livemusik ist mehr als Unterhaltung, sie ist ein friedlicher Treffpunkt f√ºr K√∂rper, Geist und Seele. Wenn Kultur √ºberall genug Raum bekommt, wird die Welt leiser im Hass und lauter im Verstehen, dann geben wir nicht denen Macht, die vom Krieg leben, sondern denen, die vom Miteinander erz√§hlen. 

ü§çüé∏üïäÔ∏è Unterst√ºtze Clubs, B√ºhnen, Stra√üenmusik, Prober√§ume, kleine Events, genau dort f√§ngt Frieden an, im echten Klang, in echten Blicken, in echter N√§he. 

ü§çüé∏üïäÔ∏è Bilder und Text @christian_weisse_digi_content 

#LongErichAndFriends #LohseSaiten #FlorianThunemann #Wundertuete #Koeln

He Booked Hawaii 5-0 From His POOL?!

Most acting coaches will tell you to stand in front of a blue wall and never use props. But sometimes, booking the role means breaking the rules.

In this video, the Self-Tape Queen breaks down the legendary story of an actor who filmed his audition for Hawaii 5-0 right inside his swimming pool‚Äîand got the part. Learn when to play it safe and when to take the creative risk that gets you cast.

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì LONDON ‚Äì THEATRE ‚Äì PROFIT SHARE**

We are casting for a new adaptation of **Sophocles‚Äô *****Antigone***, scheduled for performance in **late March / April 2026** (exact dates and venue TBC).

This is an **independent production**, developed by producer and actress **Ioanna Firaku** and co-producer and director **Una Reitere**. Due to the nature of the project, this is a **low-budget, profit-share production**, with performers paid from shared ticket-sale profits. While finances are modest, we are committed to creating a focused, rigorous, and artistically ambitious production.

**ROLES AVAILABLE**

We strongly encourage performers of **all backgrounds, ethnicities, and abilities** to apply. **Gender is not a determining factor for any role**, and all characters are open to inclusive and non-traditional casting.

All roles will involve chorus work and some devising capabilities.

**CREON / CHORUS**

*A text-heavy role.*

Newly appointed ruler of Thebes. Charismatic and authoritative, Creon believes deeply in law, order, and civic responsibility. He governs with conviction and a strong sense of duty, convinced that stability must come before personal feeling.

Rather than a villain, Creon is a leader acting from **good intentions**, whose certainty is gradually tested and fractured. As the play unfolds, moments of doubt, vulnerability, and moral conflict emerge beneath his controlled exterior. The role requires an actor capable of navigating power alongside insecurity, righteousness alongside fear, and authority alongside humanity.

Strong command of language, emotional range, and stamina for dense text are essential.

**ISMENE** / **EURYDICE / CHORUS**

Ismene: Antigone‚Äôs sister. Cautious, empathetic, and pragmatic, Ismene is torn between loyalty and fear. She represents survival, compromise, and the instinct to endure rather than resist.

Willing to move on and adapt to circumstances, Ismene‚Äôs convictions are tested when her loyalty is questioned. The role requires emotional subtlety and the ability to hold inner conflict beneath restraint.

Eurydice: Creon‚Äôs partner and Queen of Thebes. Appearing in a shorter scene towards the tragic end of the play, Eurydice carries immense emotional weight. The role demands the ability to convey grief, fear, and moral clarity through restraint, quiet strength, and a deeply grounded presence.

**HAEMON / CHORUS**

Creon‚Äôs child and Antigone‚Äôs intended. Passionate, idealistic, and emotionally conflicted, Haemon stands between generations and opposing ideologies. Courageous enough to challenge authority, they refuse to remain the dutiful child, actively confronting inherited power and breaking cycles of generational trauma.

**TEIRESIAS / GUARD / MESSENGER / CHORUS**

*A text-heavy role.*

Multiple roles requiring strong storytelling ability, versatility, and clear characterisation. **Teiresias** is the truth-bearer of the play, demanding a commanding presence and a sense of wisdom beyond human years. In contrast, the **Guard** and **Messenger** ground the world of the play in realism, offering sharp tonal shifts and, at times, moments of dark or dry humour that briefly lighten the weight of the tragedy.

**REHEARSALS & PERFORMANCE**
* Rehearsals will take place over Zoom, and in London (schedule to be confirmed collaboratively).
* Performances anticipated **late March / April 2026**.
* Venue and final dates are currently being secured.
**TO APPLY**

Please email **antigone.production2026@gmail.com** with:
* The role(s) you wish to be considered for
* A headshot **or** Spotlight link / CV

Selected applicants will be sent a short self-tape audition script.

**Audition deadline:** *08.02.2026 12am*

If you have any questions, feel free to reach out via email.

Thank you,

**Ioanna**

üé∏ Durch eine Einladung in Instagram, durch den Musiker und Schauspieler Florian Thunemann, bin ich gestern auf dieses kleine Kultur-Universum gesto√üen: 

üïäÔ∏è ‚ÄûLong Erich & Friends‚Äú trifft ‚ÄûLohse Saiten‚Äú, von Blues, Rock und Folk bis Gypsy Swing. 

ü§ç Ich habe Florian zwei Fotos gemacht und heute am PC daraus ein kleines Video geformt, Gitarrenmusik darunter, Herz dar√ºber. 

üé∏ Dabei ist mir dieser Vers in den Kopf gekommen und ich lasse ihn genau so stehen: 

üïäÔ∏è "So wie Du Bilder 
zu Geschichten formst, 
formt der Groove Dich 
zu einem Menschen, 
der wieder im Takt atmet." 

ü§ç Livemusik ist mehr als Unterhaltung, sie ist ein friedlicher Treffpunkt f√ºr K√∂rper, Geist und Seele. Wenn Kultur √ºberall genug Raum bekommt, wird die Welt leiser im Hass und lauter im Verstehen, dann geben wir nicht denen Macht, die vom Krieg leben, sondern denen, die vom Miteinander erz√§hlen. 

ü§çüé∏üïäÔ∏è Unterst√ºtze Clubs, B√ºhnen, Stra√üenmusik, Prober√§ume, kleine Events, genau dort f√§ngt Frieden an, im echten Klang, in echten Blicken, in echter N√§he. 

ü§çüé∏üïäÔ∏è Bilder und Text @christian_weisse_digi_content 

#LongErichAndFriends #LohseSaiten #FlorianThunemann #Wundertuete #Koeln

üé∏ Durch eine Einladung in Instagram, durch den Musiker und Schauspieler Florian Thunemann, bin ich gestern auf dieses kleine Kultur-Universum gesto√üen: 

üïäÔ∏è ‚ÄûLong Erich & Friends‚Äú trifft ‚ÄûLohse Saiten‚Äú, von Blues, Rock und Folk bis Gypsy Swing. 

ü§ç Ich habe Florian zwei Fotos gemacht und heute am PC daraus ein kleines Video geformt, Gitarrenmusik darunter, Herz dar√ºber. 

üé∏ Dabei ist mir dieser Vers in den Kopf gekommen und ich lasse ihn genau so stehen: 

üïäÔ∏è "So wie Du Bilder 
zu Geschichten formst, 
formt der Groove Dich 
zu einem Menschen, 
der wieder im Takt atmet." 

ü§ç Livemusik ist mehr als Unterhaltung, sie ist ein friedlicher Treffpunkt f√ºr K√∂rper, Geist und Seele. Wenn Kultur √ºberall genug Raum bekommt, wird die Welt leiser im Hass und lauter im Verstehen, dann geben wir nicht denen Macht, die vom Krieg leben, sondern denen, die vom Miteinander erz√§hlen. 

ü§çüé∏üïäÔ∏è Unterst√ºtze Clubs, B√ºhnen, Stra√üenmusik, Prober√§ume, kleine Events, genau dort f√§ngt Frieden an, im echten Klang, in echten Blicken, in echter N√§he. 

ü§çüé∏üïäÔ∏è Bilder und Text @christian_weisse_digi_content

Suche f√ºr ein Musikvideo noch eine Mitspielerin.
 
Gedreht wird zu einem etwas rockigeren Song der gut auf die breite Masse passt. 
Thema ist ‚ÄúLippenstift‚Äù Hei√üt - Du bist die sch√∂nste und darfst dich sch√∂n aufbrezeln. 
Ich Idiot stehe daneben und trage deine T√ºten und gebe dir immer eine bestfriend Meinung. 
 
Im Laufe des Songs ziehe ich das ganze aber mehr und mehr ins l√§cherliche und bring dich zum verzweifeln. 
 
Gedreht werden soll das ganze in einem Supermarkt/Drogerie einem Club oder √§hnlichen und einem Modehaus 
( Szenen beim einkaufen und nat√ºrlich vor dem Lippenstift Regal und vor dem Club ) 
Das Video soll etwas ironisch und spa√üig gestaltet werden, Konfetti schie√üen, Feenstaub werfen etc. Am Ende darfst du mir sogar zeigen wie ich selber fachlich Lippenstift auftrage. 
 
Du musst kein Profi sein 
bestenfalls im Alter von 18 ‚Äì 26 
jugendlicher Stil , schlank und am besten blond oder braunhaarig. 
 
Du solltest arrogant und eingebildet schauen k√∂nnen und etwas gestikulieren. 
Viel mehr ist nicht n√∂tig. 
Und dir das nat√ºrlich zutrauen zu drehen auch wenn es Zuschauer gibt. 
 
Drehort: L√ºneburger Umkreis 
Datum folgt wenn die Locations zugesagt haben. 
Vorweg kann nat√ºrlich ein pers√∂nliches treffen stattfinden um alles durchzukaspern. 
 
Als Dankesch√∂n bekommst du einen Gutschein deiner Wahl im Wert von 50‚Ç¨ ein Fotoshooting f√ºrs Coverbild des Songs und den gekauften Lippenstift hahahah. 
Alle entstandenen Aufnahmen/Bilder darfst du nat√ºrlich auch f√ºr eigene Zwecke verwenden.

Auf Wunsch kann ich dir auch schon ein paar Songausschnitte zeigen :)

items.text:
CASTING CALL ‚Äì LIVERPOOL ACTORS WANTED 

We're casting for "They Were All Some Mothers' Sons" ‚Äì a powerful true story returning to the stage at Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot in May 2026.

This sell-out production tells the remarkable true story of German POWs detained in Huyton during WWII who fell in love with local women and chose to stay, becoming part of our community. 

Previously performed to packed houses in Liverpool and Germany.

Roles available:

 Jean ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Eleanor ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Marjorie ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Joey ‚Äì Young British RAF pilot, male, playing age 18-24

 Mother ‚Äì female, playing age 40+

 Father ‚Äì male, playing age 40+

Key dates:

 Auditions: First week of February

 Rehearsals: Mid-March to show

 Performances: 1st, 2nd May 2026 (possible 3rd date)

 Venue: Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot

This is a paid role (profit share)

This is Prescot's own heritage story‚Äîtold in the heart of Knowsley, where it all happened over 80 years ago. We're looking for passionate local talent to bring this living history to life.

To apply: Send your CV and headshot to howl.michael1963@yahoo.co.uk specifying which role and which production you want to audition for.

Please prepare a 2-minute monologue of your choice for audition.

CASTING CALL ‚Äì LIVERPOOL ACTORS WANTED üé≠

We're casting for "They Were All Some Mothers' Sons" ‚Äì a powerful true story returning to the stage at Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot in May 2026.

This sell-out production tells the remarkable true story of German POWs detained in Huyton during WWII who fell in love with local women and chose to stay, becoming part of our community. Previously performed to packed houses in Liverpool and Germany.

Roles available:
üé¨ Jean ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25
üé¨ Eleanor ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25
üé¨ Marjorie ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25
üé¨ Joey ‚Äì Young British RAF pilot, male, playing age 18-24
üé¨ Mother ‚Äì female, playing age 40+
üé¨ Father ‚Äì male, playing age 40+

Key dates:
üìÖ Auditions: First week of February
üìÖ Rehearsals: Mid-March to show
üìÖ Performances: 1st, 2nd May 2026 (possible 3rd date)
üìç Venue: Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot

This is a paid role (profit share)

This is Prescot's own heritage story‚Äîtold in the heart of Knowsley, where it all happened over 80 years ago. We're looking for passionate local talent to bring this living history to life.

To apply: Send your CV and headshot to howl.michael1963@yahoo.co.uk specifying which role and which production you want to audition for.

Please prepare a 2-minute monologue of your choice for audition.

‚ÄúAs a kid I once went to a film and I was bored with it. ¬†I pretended for a minute that I was hiding in a closet watching the event through a keyhole. ¬†All of a sudden the entire reality of the film changed. ¬†Up until that point my imagination made the film a real event, I wasn‚Äôt watching a performance. ¬†The minute I watched it through the keyhole, certain performances became interesting and real and others became patently false. ¬†I felt that they [the bad performers] were currying favor from an audience. ¬†My feeling was, ‚ÄòThey don‚Äôt know I‚Äôm out here so why are they acting for me?‚Äô That gave me my first gauge, my first ethos, for good and bad work.‚Äù

Alan Arkin from The Actor Speaks, edited by Janet Sonenberg

NEW YEAR, NEW CLASS!!! 

Let‚Äôs explore the depth, boundaries, authenticity and grow the range of your acting. 

START THE YEAR INSPIRED! 

NOW is the perfect time to sign up for all or any of the 3 steps our comprehensive CERTIFICATE PROGRAM! 

STEP 1: PRIVATE COACHING - 

6x1hr sessions, learn or re-enforce the essentials, with trusted process preparation techniques and direction, we prepare and tape contrasting monologues. Add to your reel!

STEP 2: SEMIPRIVATE, SCENE-STUDY: 
3x2hr sessions. I partner you, we review and apply the preparation techniques. We tape 2 scenes with playback, notes and direction, with a focus on on-camera technique - living in the scene! Add to your reel! 
 
Or .. alternate STEP 2:  SIGN UP FOR THE JANUARY THURSDAY NIGHT SCENE-STUDY CLASS: 
Feb. 5, 12, 19, 26: 6-9 pm. 

We‚Äôre preparing and taping scenes, telling compelling stories, applying foundational, analytical preparation techniques, with a focus on screen acting skills, using 2 cameras. 

STEP 3: THE SUCCESSFUL AUDITIONS WORKSHOP:
2 days, sharpen your audition skills, plus SELF-TAPE AUDITIONS, for commercials and film and TV series, we tape your 2 auditions, with critique, coaching, direction and demonstration. Next: FEB. 22nd & 23rd, repeats every 3rd mth. 

CERTIFICATE PROGRAM (ALL 3 STEPS):
Comprehensive training! 

Add tape for your reel! Agent referrals! For prices and more information:
416 294-3754 / bongoproductions.com

items.text:
Actors ‚Äî stop planning your scenes.

If you‚Äôve already decided how every line will land, where you‚Äôll move, when you‚Äôll ‚Äúshow emotion‚Äù‚Ä¶ you‚Äôre not acting. You‚Äôre demonstrating an idea of acting.

Real screen performance lives in reaction, not choreography.

Start working from this instead:
React to what you see.
React to what you hear.
React to what you think.
React to what you feel.

Let the moment mess with you. Let the other person affect you. Let your thoughts interrupt you. That‚Äôs where truth shows up.

The best scenes don‚Äôt go how the actor expected ‚Äî they go somewhere alive. Somewhere human. Somewhere you couldn‚Äôt have planned.

Instinct over control.
Impulse over polish.
Connection over ‚Äúgetting it right‚Äù.

That‚Äôs when casting actually leans in.

üîó Link in bio: linktr.ee/mattzina

#ActingForCamera #ActorMindset #ScreenActing #ActingTips #ActorsLife

items.text:
Hello everyone, 

Join the team at North West End Acting School!

We are looking for an experienced Acting Teacher to join our ranks and teach our adult group acting classes.

What we are looking for: 

- Professional acting training

- Professional acting experience in theatre and TV

- Experience in working to lesson plans and/or a curriculum

- Be enthusiastic, energetic and friendly

- Can teach techniques and exercises from - Meisner, Uta Hagen, Stanislavski

-  The post holder will also be responsible for the welfare of the students and the opening and closing of the venue.

- Candidates should be DBS checked and have Public liability insurance.

A bit more about the role:

Classes take place in Chester between 7:15pm and 9:15pm and run over a period of ten weeks. You will be working with groups of maximum 20 students. The courses run regularly throughout the year.

We are looking for someone who is dynamic and adaptable, able to work with a variety of people from all backgrounds and ages and with a passion for sharing the joy of acting. 

If that sounds like you, please send us your CV and cover letter to info@northwestendactingschool.co.uk

------------------------

## Casting Call: Couple Talent for Lifestyle Brand Video (Squamish)

We‚Äôre casting **2 on-camera performers** to play a **couple arriving at a vacation home** for a lifestyle brand video shoot in **Squamish, BC**. 

Shoot Details
* Location: **Squamish, BC**
* Date:** Wed Feb 4th**
* Duration: **4 hours**
* Rate: **$400 flat** per person
* Union status: **Non-union**
* Usage: **Brand marketing** (web + social)

Roles (2 Talent)

**Couple (Ages 35‚Äì55)**
* Fit, active-looking individuals with an approachable, outdoorsy vibe
* Comfortable on camera with light direction
* Real couples encouraged, but not required

How to Apply

Please email the following to tom@setsail.ca:
1. **Name + age**
2. **Recent photos** (headshot + full-body; phone pics are fine)
3. **Any on-camera experience**
4. **If applying as a real couple**, include both names and photos together (optional)
5. **Availability confirmation** for the shoot window

items.text:
Casting for leading Man/Leading Lady young adult early to mid-20's.
I'm shooting another short vertical demo for two days between now and February 8 (dates TBA) and am looking for two non-union actors with comedic acting chops, to play out the dialogue in this romantic comedy (a few scenes).

Shooting will be in downtown and East Vancouver, there will be a rehearsal day after actors are off-book and then we shoot.

This is a demo, voluntary, for actors reel and directing sample.

If interested, please email me your photo, resume and availability to castingproject604@gmail.com.

**CASTING CALL - Non-union **

Looking for Slavic/Eastern European looking actors for small, non-speaking roles in short film, During Winter, I Thought of My Father, a Russian language short film by Daniil Vasilyev. 

**ACTORS DO NOT NEED TO SPEAK RUSSIAN AS THE ROLES ARE NON-SPEAKING. **

**Main Shoot Dates: Feb 14th-16th, 2026 **

**Descriptions: **

**Young Russian Man, early 20s: **Need him available for a day in the week leading up to Feb 14th for a photoshoot. 
Specific date TBD, but we are flexible and willing to work with actor's schedule. 

**Older Russian Woman, 50s-60s: **Needed for photoshoot Feb 16th. 

**Older Russian Man, 40s-60s: **Needed for filming Feb 14th, 15th, photoshoot on the 16th. Non-speaking role, will be playing main character's father. 

**Compensation: **IMDb credit, post-film credit, food provided as well as transport if required**. **

**Location: **Greater Vancouver Area 

**If interested, please send an email to ****duringwinter26@gmail.com ****with any headshots or good pictures of yourself, your reel (if you have one), and stats (height, eye colour, etc). **

** **

items.text:
**CASTING CALL ‚Äì LONDON ‚Äì THEATRE ‚Äì PROFIT SHARE**

We are casting for a new adaptation of **Sophocles‚Äô *****Antigone***, scheduled for performance in **late March / April 2026** (exact dates and venue TBC).

This is an **independent production**, developed by producer and actress **Ioanna Firaku** and co-producer and director **Una Reitere**. Due to the nature of the project, this is a **low-budget, profit-share production**, with performers paid from shared ticket-sale profits. While finances are modest, we are committed to creating a focused, rigorous, and artistically ambitious production.

**ROLES AVAILABLE**

We strongly encourage performers of **all backgrounds, ethnicities, and abilities** to apply. **Gender is not a determining factor for any role**, and all characters are open to inclusive and non-traditional casting.

All roles will involve chorus work and some devising capabilities.

**CREON / CHORUS**

*A text-heavy role.*

Newly appointed ruler of Thebes. Charismatic and authoritative, Creon believes deeply in law, order, and civic responsibility. He governs with conviction and a strong sense of duty, convinced that stability must come before personal feeling.

Rather than a villain, Creon is a leader acting from **good intentions**, whose certainty is gradually tested and fractured. As the play unfolds, moments of doubt, vulnerability, and moral conflict emerge beneath his controlled exterior. The role requires an actor capable of navigating power alongside insecurity, righteousness alongside fear, and authority alongside humanity.

Strong command of language, emotional range, and stamina for dense text are essential.

**ISMENE** / **EURYDICE / CHORUS**

Ismene: Antigone‚Äôs sister. Cautious, empathetic, and pragmatic, Ismene is torn between loyalty and fear. She represents survival, compromise, and the instinct to endure rather than resist.

Willing to move on and adapt to circumstances, Ismene‚Äôs convictions are tested when her loyalty is questioned. The role requires emotional subtlety and the ability to hold inner conflict beneath restraint.

Eurydice: Creon‚Äôs partner and Queen of Thebes. Appearing in a shorter scene towards the tragic end of the play, Eurydice carries immense emotional weight. The role demands the ability to convey grief, fear, and moral clarity through restraint, quiet strength, and a deeply grounded presence.

**HAEMON / CHORUS**

Creon‚Äôs child and Antigone‚Äôs intended. Passionate, idealistic, and emotionally conflicted, Haemon stands between generations and opposing ideologies. Courageous enough to challenge authority, they refuse to remain the dutiful child, actively confronting inherited power and breaking cycles of generational trauma.

**TEIRESIAS / GUARD / MESSENGER / CHORUS**

*A text-heavy role.*

Multiple roles requiring strong storytelling ability, versatility, and clear characterisation. **Teiresias** is the truth-bearer of the play, demanding a commanding presence and a sense of wisdom beyond human years. In contrast, the **Guard** and **Messenger** ground the world of the play in realism, offering sharp tonal shifts and, at times, moments of dark or dry humour that briefly lighten the weight of the tragedy.

**REHEARSALS & PERFORMANCE**
* Rehearsals will take place over Zoom, and in London (schedule to be confirmed collaboratively).
* Performances anticipated **late March / April 2026**.
* Venue and final dates are currently being secured.
**TO APPLY**

Please email **antigone.production2026@gmail.com** with:
* The role(s) you wish to be considered for
* A headshot **or** Spotlight link / CV

Selected applicants will be sent a short self-tape audition script.

**Audition deadline:** *08.02.2026 12am*

If you have any questions, feel free to reach out via email.

Thank you,

Ioanna

29-31 January in Berlin.

In this workshop Antonia Cezara CioazƒÉ and Jakob Nielsen are sharing their personal training called IMAGINING WITH THE BODY-MIND which they have developed together with their director, Eugenio Barba since January 2022. 

The training is based on the use of imagination in the pre-expressive level of the creative process of the actor.

Through guided work in embodied presence and spontaneous exploration, participants learn to access their intuitive responses and channel them into focused, expressive action. The participants will explore composition by practising varied ways of walking and dancing. 

They can use the exercises in their personal practice order to enhance their stage presence. The exercises are crafted to let participants tap into their own associations, opening pathways to authentic expression on stage.

More details: [https://imaginingbodymind.carrd.co](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fimaginingbodymind.carrd.co%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQQMjIyMDM5MTc4ODIwMDg5MgABHmwgV6ATObZ3kmmCDbESsuL7JJ8ikSuIXxovuJRvRolTYi2wK_hX9m28KHjI_aem_KXbemAkoiwLRQWeL6zJhhA&h=AT1H9OBzjQyXL6cmaONDfv0q223N8TRU6_uKZ4Av-zAritd4t408rQzHkwAUTZW17V52l6-dScMAYaAK3IADk0mHta98eae8pHcZF6NotDXMduXrRRMtM6A-fjhv27QqroYSnuopKrBSfoLQC88NnWZuHHptDA&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT3Lu1X4iM3PjxlrZwntZon8UXjvDj_OF40QYKaLurcg3zTswjbkbQ0I37wr9A_DnWB-dMmSp7Gjfv2bdzW3Hz4xBdeGCsrCaS_q8-vhY0wx-LZJ9XPS6WW6h5LFRkzxkA_7KEqO49p2eU6mrqpY3XF0Tzidw2rwKLC-HsjMOmsQYyYryoA2JDveMds)

29-31 January in Berlin.

In this workshop Antonia Cezara CioazƒÉ and Jakob Nielsen are sharing their personal training called IMAGINING WITH THE BODY-MIND which they have developed together with their director, Eugenio Barba since January 2022. 

The training is based on the use of imagination in the pre-expressive level of the creative process of the actor.

Through guided work in embodied presence and spontaneous exploration, participants learn to access their intuitive responses and channel them into focused, expressive action. The participants will explore composition by practising varied ways of walking and dancing. 

They can use the exercises in their personal practice order to enhance their stage presence. The exercises are crafted to let participants tap into their own associations, opening pathways to authentic expression on stage.

More details: [https://imaginingbodymind.carrd.co](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fimaginingbodymind.carrd.co%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQQMjIyMDM5MTc4ODIwMDg5MgABHmwgV6ATObZ3kmmCDbESsuL7JJ8ikSuIXxovuJRvRolTYi2wK_hX9m28KHjI_aem_KXbemAkoiwLRQWeL6zJhhA&h=AT1H9OBzjQyXL6cmaONDfv0q223N8TRU6_uKZ4Av-zAritd4t408rQzHkwAUTZW17V52l6-dScMAYaAK3IADk0mHta98eae8pHcZF6NotDXMduXrRRMtM6A-fjhv27QqroYSnuopKrBSfoLQC88NnWZuHHptDA&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT3Lu1X4iM3PjxlrZwntZon8UXjvDj_OF40QYKaLurcg3zTswjbkbQ0I37wr9A_DnWB-dMmSp7Gjfv2bdzW3Hz4xBdeGCsrCaS_q8-vhY0wx-LZJ9XPS6WW6h5LFRkzxkA_7KEqO49p2eU6mrqpY3XF0Tzidw2rwKLC-HsjMOmsQYyYryoA2JDveMds)

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

CASTING CALL - ASAP

25/01/25

The Party No One Wanted (Short Film)

**A dark comedy about grief and family relationships.**

Robbie and Mary have to get through an excruciating memorial that has a DJ, karaoke and a pregnancy announcement / gender reveal planned by their half sister Lisa.

* **Shooting 6th - 9th March in TW19**
* Auditions in Elephant and Castle within the next few weeks
* **Travel Expenses Paid**
* Student film hoping to go to Film festivals
* **Robbie **(28-38yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Emotionally withdrawn but has a kind heart, he's holding it together for Mary and his Dad
* **Steve** (57-70yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Mary, Robbie and Lisa‚Äôs dad doesn‚Äôt get involved in the arguing he‚Äôs still devastated by the loss of his wife but insists he‚Äôs fine.
* **Lisa** (39-47yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Self centred and definitely doesn‚Äôt know whats appropriate at a memorial. 
* **Natalie** (49-65yrs)
   * A close family friend who has taken on a bit of a motherly role to everyone, kind and soft spoken.
* **Bill** (50-65yrs) 
   * The drunk best friend of steve who has awful timing for his awkward comments. Very funny character

**Character Bios: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing)** **

**Director‚Äôs Statement: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing) 

Email: [mhmollie0303@icloud.com](mailto:mhmollie0303@icloud.com) for further details

items.text:
CASTING CALL for a Short film *RYLIE* 
A Dramatic Sci/Fi short film about a couple through Grief and the Afterlife, funded by the Toronto Arts Council. Paid. Meals included. 

Non-Union

Shooting In Mid-May in Toronto, ON, Canada.

LOGLINE: Glitches in her old footage drag a grieving woman back through the stages of loss, forcing her to confront the remnants of a relationship she can‚Äôt release and the growing gaps in her own story. 

**DAVID: SUPPORTING**

Late 20s / early 30s. Stylish but unshowy. Quiet confidence. A lived-in edge.  Creative, sensitive, observant. Carries traces of a past life: recovery, scars, depth.

Once deeply connected to RYLIE before his tragic accident. Appears both as her boyfriend and as a ghost ‚Äî intimate, restrained, emotionally present rather than overtly ‚Äúspooky.‚Äù

A modern romantic with a subtle punk ethos (attitude, not costume). (2 full days) $250/day

**ROOMMATE: SUPPORTING**

Early‚Äìmid 20s. Social, independent, and perpetually in motion.  juggling plans, group chats. Loves a bit of gossip and the comfort of communal chaos.

Frequently misses the quieter emotional beats in the room, not out of insensitivity but because she assumes everything will sort itself out. Brings warmth, momentum, and gentle comic relief to RYLIE‚Äôs interior world. (1 day) $250/day

**3 TRENDY FRIENDS: 2 FEATURED EXTRAS +1 BIT PART**

18 to mid 20s. all ethnicities / any genders. Three close friends, think subcultures: ravers, bandmates, skaters, goths with 2yk style. A small speaking role will be for one of the friends. Please submit separately or as a group if you can. Individual submissions will be accepted as well. Pay is based on 1 hr of shooting. $100 per person plus meal. Estimated commitment is 3-4 hours.

Please submit self-tapes via Backstage, Actors Access, or through ryliecasting@gmail.com, and please share with anyone who might be interested. thanks!

https://www.backstage.com/casting/rylie-a-scifi-drama-funded-by-tac-3072572/

items.text:
Actors ‚Äî stop planning your scenes.

If you‚Äôve already decided how every line will land, where you‚Äôll move, when you‚Äôll ‚Äúshow emotion‚Äù‚Ä¶ you‚Äôre not acting. You‚Äôre demonstrating an idea of acting.

Real screen performance lives in reaction, not choreography.

Start working from this instead:
React to what you see.
React to what you hear.
React to what you think.
React to what you feel.

Let the moment mess with you. Let the other person affect you. Let your thoughts interrupt you. That‚Äôs where truth shows up.

The best scenes don‚Äôt go how the actor expected ‚Äî they go somewhere alive. Somewhere human. Somewhere you couldn‚Äôt have planned.

Instinct over control.
Impulse over polish.
Connection over ‚Äúgetting it right‚Äù.

That‚Äôs when casting actually leans in.

üîó Link in bio: linktr.ee/mattzina

#ActingForCamera #ActorMindset #ScreenActing #ActingTips #ActorsLife

items.text:
**CASTING CALL ‚Äì LONDON ‚Äì THEATRE ‚Äì PROFIT SHARE**

We are casting for a new adaptation of **Sophocles‚Äô *****Antigone***, scheduled for performance in **late March / April 2026** (exact dates and venue TBC).

This is an **independent production**, developed by producer and actress **Ioanna Firaku** and co-producer and director **Una Reitere**. Due to the nature of the project, this is a **low-budget, profit-share production**, with performers paid from shared ticket sale profits. While finances are modest, we are committed to creating a focused, rigorous, and artistically ambitious production.

## **ROLES AVAILABLE**

We strongly encourage performers of **all backgrounds, ethnicities, and abilities** to apply. **Gender is not a determining factor for any role**, and all characters are open to inclusive and non-traditional casting.

All roles will involve chorus work and some devising capabilities.

**CREON / CHORUS**

*A text-heavy role.*

Newly appointed ruler of Thebes. Charismatic and authoritative, Creon believes deeply in law, order, and civic responsibility. He governs with conviction and a strong sense of duty, convinced that stability must come before personal feeling.

Rather than a villain, Creon is a leader acting from **good intentions**, whose certainty is gradually tested and fractured. As the play unfolds, moments of doubt, vulnerability, and moral conflict emerge beneath his controlled exterior. The role requires an actor capable of navigating power alongside insecurity, righteousness alongside fear, and authority alongside humanity.

Strong command of language, emotional range, and stamina for dense text are essential.

**ISMENE** / **EURYDICE / CHORUS**

Ismene: Antigone‚Äôs sister. Cautious, empathetic, and pragmatic, Ismene is torn between loyalty and fear. She represents survival, compromise, and the instinct to endure rather than resist.

Willing to move on and adapt to circumstances, Ismene‚Äôs convictions are tested when her loyalty is questioned. The role requires emotional subtlety and the ability to hold inner conflict beneath restraint.

Eurydice: Creon‚Äôs partner and Queen of Thebes. Appearing in a shorter scene towards the tragic end of the play, Eurydice carries immense emotional weight. The role demands the ability to convey grief, fear, and moral clarity through restraint, quiet strength, and a deeply grounded presence.

**HAEMON / CHORUS**

Creon‚Äôs child and Antigone‚Äôs intended. Passionate, idealistic, and emotionally conflicted, Haemon stands between generations and opposing ideologies. Courageous enough to challenge authority, they refuse to remain the dutiful child, actively confronting inherited power and breaking cycles of generational trauma.

**TEIRESIAS / GUARD / MESSENGER / CHORUS**

*A text-heavy role.*

Multiple roles requiring strong storytelling ability, versatility, and clear characterisation. **Teiresias** is the truth-bearer of the play, demanding a commanding presence and a sense of wisdom beyond human years. In contrast, the **Guard** and **Messenger** ground the world of the play in realism, offering sharp tonal shifts and, at times, moments of dark or dry humour that briefly lighten the weight of the tragedy.

**REHEARSALS & PERFORMANCE**
* Rehearsals will take place over Zoom, and in London (schedule to be confirmed collaboratively).
* Performances anticipated **late March / April 2026**.
* Venue and final dates are currently being secured.
**TO APPLY**

Please email **antigone.production2026@gmail.com** with:
* The role(s) you wish to be considered for
* A headshot **or** Spotlight link / CV

Selected applicants will be sent a short self-tape audition script.

**Audition deadline:** *08.02.2026 12am*

If you have any questions, feel free to reach out via email.

Thank you,

**Una**

items.text:
**CASTING CALL**

*Lead Roles for Interactive Game + Vertical Drama Production*

**Project: **The Fame Game 2: L.A. Heartbreaker

**Production: **Snail Games / Interactive Films

**Location: **Los Angeles, CA

**Shoot Dates: **March 2026 (approx. 20 days)

**Rate: **$500‚Äì$800/day

**ABOUT THE PROJECT**

This is an interactive video game production combining romance, comedy, and drama with multiple branching storylines and endings. The project involves extensive ensemble work, romantic/comedic chemistry across multiple pairings, and emotionally complex character arcs. Open to all ethnicities except where noted. Acting experience is not required, and active social media presence is a plus.

**AUDITION PROCESS**

**Round 1: **Virtual Interview (unpaid)

**Round 2: **In-person audition in Los Angeles ($100/30 min, paid) or self-tape if unable to travel

**Talent invited to round 2 must:**
* Participate in an online voting campaign
* Sign release and waiver allowing use of audition materials for voting and promotional purposes

**MIA ‚Äî Female Lead**

Age: 23 | Ethnicity: Open

Gentle and competent mentor with a cool, wild streak. Professional exterior that gradually reveals a shy, jealous romantic side through interactions with the male lead.

**Requirements:**
* Sophisticated demeanor; ability to convey subtle emotional shifts
* Stunt/action experience a plus (driving scenes)

**CAMILLE ‚Äî Female Lead**

Age: 24 | Ethnicity: Open

A confident, bold print model who plays games with love but transforms into someone capable of genuine emotion. Sexy, fiery, and provocative, but ultimately vulnerable.

**Requirements:**
* Model experience a plus
* Comfortable with flirtatious/sensual scenes
* Strong emotional range

**LIN MUYUN ‚Äî Female Lead**

Age: 27 | Ethnicity: Mixed / Half Asian

Gentle and elegant on the surface, highly possessive underneath. Carries childhood trauma and develops complicated feelings for her stepbrother. Borderline obsessive but deeply sympathetic.

**Requirements:**
* Comfortable with intimate/intense emotional scenes
* Ability to portray psychological complexity

**ROLES**
**SHUHAN HO ‚Äî Male Lead**

Age: 23 | Ethnicity: Chinese / East Asian

An ordinary international student mistaken for a wealthy heir with an identical appearance. Vain and drawn to glamour, but kind-hearted beneath the surface. Awkward yet sincere, constantly juggling multiple romantic entanglements while navigating his double identity.

**Requirements:**
* Strong comedic timing; ability to portray vulnerability and growth
* Chemistry with multiple female leads
* Must play two characters (Shuhan Ho and Shuhan ‚ÄúRichie‚Äù Ho)
* Mandarin Chinese fluency required

**SHUHAN ‚ÄúRICHIE‚Äù HO ‚Äî Male Supporting**

Age: 23 | Ethnicity: Chinese / East Asian

The true rich heir‚Äîand a complete emotional predator. Hedonistic, selfish, and unapologetically cruel in matters of love. Free of guilt or conscience, he is the protagonist's dark mirror and the original source of the story's turmoil.

**Requirements: **Same as Shuhan Ho (dual role)

**SUSANNA ‚Äî Female Lead**

Age: 21 | Ethnicity: East Asian

A pampered rich heiress, innocent and stubborn, completely clueless about everyday life. Outwardly confident but inwardly fragile and insecure. Clumsy yet endearing in her attempts to win love.

**Requirements:**
* Ability to balance comedy with emotional vulnerability
* Physical comedy skills preferred
* Must deliver Chinese, Japanese, or Korean dialogue with authentic/native pronunciation (fluency not required)

**LI SISI ‚Äî Female Lead**

Age: 22 | Ethnicity: Chinese / East Asian

Pure, kind, girl-next-door type. The male lead's moral compass and childhood sweetheart. Sweet but capable of jealousy and testing born from insecurity.

**Requirements:**
* Natural, understated performance style
* Chemistry with male lead; ability to convey heartbreak
* Must deliver Chinese dialogue with authentic/native pronunciation

**TO SUBMIT**
1. Headshot and full-body photo
2. Acting resume

**Send submissions to: **casting@rarefloweragency.com

**Deadline: Feb 8, 2026 (12PM, PST)**

Hello everyone. In keeping with the spirit of this wonderful group and self promotion like everyone else....
Check out my latest 2026 showreels, 2026 Voiceover demo, other videos and an updated list of credits that reflect my journey over the years in the world of acting.

I've a few interesting gigs under my belt over the last 6 months including 2 projects in Derry and one in Belfast with NI Screen respectfully and ALWAYS looking to work with ambitious and creatively driven people. 

I'm working on actively developing my own projects at a high standard. And have a Tv series and Documentary project in various stages of development also. So I don't wait for the grass to grow under my feet. 

Check out my updated Spotlight Profile here: 

https://app.spotlight.com/9178-9057-1772?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAAR115-d7hRxs_gEXgjRM2bkqdaz76JyKSnHZTXL9W_wKShJ7vwM14OsNGRY_aem_LN9wUELiWL6SzKp

If you‚Äôre looking for a dedicated Actor, Mc, Presenter or Podcast host, with good improv skills and experience for your next project or know someone who is, let's connect! I'm excited to explore new opportunities. üòÉ üé• 

For Voiceover check out www.Soundcloud.com/pblvo 

For more information about me generally visit. 

https://linktr.ee/PaulBLennox

Thank you for your interest Have a Brilliant 2026. You deserve it.

items.text:
Reminder. Audition Monday coming. 26th. Wanted: 2 actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays.

We are looking for two versatile actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays: ‚ÄúThe Balled of Crooked Lane‚Äù by Tom Mclennan and ‚ÄúWake‚Äù by Day Sheehan, to be performed on Wed 25th February (the awards evening) at the Gladstone Theatre, Port Sunlight. Both play were part of the Liverpool Fringe and won numerous nominations for best play etc.

Plays and parts descriptions.
‚ÄúThe Ballad of Crooked Lane‚Äù is set on the day Edward Rushton, prominent anti-slavery campaigner and blind poet, now well into middle age, awaits eye surgery to regain his sight. While waiting, he goes over his eventful life with his friend and biographer, William Shepherd, the Minister of Gateacre Chapel.

The part: The actor would play Billy the Ballad-monger in one important scene, a lively, upfront character full of humour, a seller of broadside ballads and casual acquaintance of Rushton. The actor would also fulfil several other small roles and be fully active on stage in what is an ensemble production.

‚ÄúWake‚Äù When Daniel Anderson finds himself in an unfamiliar place with fragments of the previous night missing from his memory, he must piece together the truth of what happened. This experimental drama explores themes of guilt, responsibility, and the price of self-deception in a world where nothing is quite what it seems.

The part: POLICE OFFICER 2 (Any gender, 30s+) - The psychological manipulator who probes emotional wounds. The actor needs to be versatile as this role requires them to be multi faceted

No particular age or even gender is necessarily required We are looking for  actors who can bring the characters to life.

Audition date: Monday 26th January 7pm. Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA

Contact info@valleytheatre.co.uk or turn up on the night. No prep needed. audition will consist of short extract from the script.

Please note: There is no fee for these roles. Hopefully the material and occasion will appeal.

Casting call for a Scouse crime comedy/tragedy short with award winning script
Hoping to shoot in summer 2026, dependent on funding. I‚Äôm looking to fill the remaining three roles for the gang of four lads that are essentially the main focus of the film (besides Cookie, the lead role). These are chief supporting roles, and all roles in the film are paid.

No prior acting experience required. If any of the roles leap out at you, I encourage you to go for it. These particular roles definitely need to be scousers - or if you‚Äôre that one-in-a-million person who can fake it üòâ

I‚Äôd prefer if you used the email from the ad below if you want to get in touch, but I‚Äôll still check my inbox on here too anyway.

More roles will be posted soon.

Thanks.

**Temat 6 ‚Äì ‚Äò‚ÄôLara Croft ‚Äò‚Äô**

# [CASTING CALL] NON-UNION BG FOR VERTICAL MICRODRAMA

Looking for background performer with basketball experience for the following dates:

**SHOOTING DATES: **JAN 29, 31, FEB 1-3

**LOCATION: **Abbotsford, North Vancouver and Squamish (fuel compensation available for travel to Abbotsford and Squamish)

*Must have reliable vehicle

* Non-Union
* POC encouraged
* Age 19-25
* 5'10" to 6'1"
* Must have their own basketball shoes
* Intermediate/advanced basketball skill set

Pay rate: $144.80/8hr, OT applied thereafter.

If interested, please email: **casting@yymediaco.com**, using "**The Comeback Play - Basketball Player**" in the subject line. In the message, please include your **height, availability, a brief description of your basketball experience, and agency** (if applicable). As well as **a headshot**. 

Thank you in advance!

message.text:
SONGS FROM LIFE with Stefanie Rummel  @adlfringe & @newcastlefringe Fringe 
Let the melodies carry you... the stories transform you.

AUSTRALIAN PREMIERE: 
https://adelaidefringe.com.au/fringetix/songs-from-life-af2026

Award-winning singer Stefanie Rummel takes you on a captivating musical journey ‚Äî from the caf√©s of Paris to the cabarets of Berlin, and the clubs of Manhattan. 
Featuring songs in the style of Piaf, Weill, Sondheim, and her own original works.
Through stories and songs, Stefanie ignites longing, laughter, and love ‚Äî in a show that touches hearts and minds.
Seven chansons were written by Stefanie Rummel (lyrics & music). They were arranged and produced in collaboration with Tom Schl√ºter (pianist & music producer).
Praised as ‚Äúsoul-touching‚Äù and ‚Äúbrilliant showmanship‚Äù, Stefanie Rummel has enchanted audiences across the US, UK, Europe, and Australia.
‚ÄúYou beautifully blended your life experiences and stories into a creative music journey with such thoughtful themes. Your insights and heartfelt messages truly moved me and continue to echo in my heart long after the show.‚Äù
‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ ‚ÄúOutstanding Voice‚Äù  TheReviewHub
‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ ‚ÄúRevelation‚Äù  LondonTheatre1

A sparkling celebration of life, music, and connection ‚Äî cabaret at its most heartfelt.

Europe‚Äôs Award-Winning Voice:
https://youtu.be/tplyVnOjMxo

items.text:
CASTING CALL - small indie film shooting in Colorado Springs on January 30. There are 2 scenes shooting that day. 
1. Coffee Shop: 12 people, portraying patrons, students, etc., dressed in comfortable clothes, 1p-5p.
2. Hospital: 3 people, portraying EMS personnel, dressed in scrubs, 6p-9p.

Rate: IMDB credit, crafty available, footage upon completion

Production Company: Legacy Landmarks Studio, Golden Hour Grid

Title: The Last Frame

Logline: A military veteran finds happiness and purpose after meeting the woman who changes his life - but after a sudden accident and one irreversible mistake, their love collapses into devastating consequences. 

Genre: Drama

Run Time: 10 minutes

Gedreht wird zu einem etwas rockigeren Song der gut auf die breite Masse passt. 
Thema ist ‚ÄúLippenstift‚Äù Hei√üt - Du bist die sch√∂nste und darfst dich sch√∂n aufbrezeln. 
Ich Idiot stehe daneben und trage deine T√ºten und gebe dir immer eine bestfriend Meinung. 
 
Im Laufe des Songs ziehe ich das ganze aber mehr und mehr ins l√§cherliche und bring dich zum verzweifeln. 
 
Gedreht werden soll das ganze in einem Supermarkt/Drogerie einem Club oder √§hnlichen und einem Modehaus 
( Szenen beim einkaufen und nat√ºrlich vor dem Lippenstift Regal und vor dem Club ) 
Das Video soll etwas ironisch und spa√üig gestaltet werden, Konfetti schie√üen, Feenstaub werfen etc. Am Ende darfst du mir sogar zeigen wie ich selber fachlich Lippenstift auftrage. 
 
Du musst kein Profi sein 
bestenfalls im Alter von 18 ‚Äì 26 
jugendlicher Stil , schlank und am besten blond oder braunhaarig. 
 
Du solltest arrogant und eingebildet schauen k√∂nnen und etwas gestikulieren. 
Viel mehr ist nicht n√∂tig. 
Und dir das nat√ºrlich zutrauen zu drehen auch wenn es Zuschauer gibt. 
 
Drehort: L√ºneburger Umkreis 
Datum folgt wenn die Locations zugesagt haben. 
Vorweg kann nat√ºrlich ein pers√∂nliches treffen stattfinden um alles durchzukaspern. 
 
Als Dankesch√∂n bekommst du einen Gutschein deiner Wahl im Wert von 50‚Ç¨ ein Fotoshooting f√ºrs Coverbild des Songs und den gekauften Lippenstift hahahah. 
Alle entstandenen Aufnahmen/Bilder darfst du nat√ºrlich auch f√ºr eigene Zwecke verwenden.

Hello everyone. In keeping with the spirit of this wonderful group and self promotion like everyone else....
Check out my latest 2026 showreels, 2026 Voiceover demo, other videos and an updated list of credits that reflect my journey over the years in the world of acting.

**CASTING CALL FOR TWITCH LIVE STREAM**

This casting is for talent to appear in a live Twitch stream hosted by well-known streamers. 

**Location: **TBD, Los Angeles, CA

**Pay: **$75/5hours

**Shoot Date: **Friday, 1/30, from 5 PM to 9 PM

**Looking For: **Men of all ages, races, sexualities 

**More Info:** In this Twitch live stream, our hosts will test their GAYDAR by talking with a group of men and trying to guess if they're gay or straight. The goal is to show that gay doesn't have a specific look, so we'd love to see non-stereotypical representations of what both gay and straight can look like! We are seeking men of all ages, races, and sexualities who want to showcase their fun and unique personalities!

**How to Submit:** Fill out the following Google Form
